Running has never been one of my favorite hobbies, but I somehow felt like I could use it today.
I quickly grabbed my sweatshirt, took a bite out of my ham sandwich, and left the kitchen. The first few steps were horrible. With each leg lift, I felt like I was carrying some kind of weight that was only making my journey harder. In fact, it wasn't my body that was heavy, it was my soul carrying the ruins of our conversation from yesterday. 
It was not the first time he had hurt me. Of course, not the last, I was sure. He keeps pushing me ...
